{
  "doc_id": "18371",
  "text": "The Balters Bionator is a functional appliance designed and introduced by Wilhelm Balters in 1960 and is still one of many functional removable appliances used for correction of Class II division 1 malocclusions [CITATION_1] RudzkiJanson & Noachtar, 1998; [CITATION_2] ). There are various reasons for bionator use, but the main reason is its low cost and simplicity of its construction. In developing countries, these reasons have a positive social influence and this benefit from bionator treatment can have a wide societal scope.",
  "correct_citation": {
